etymologies: mid 18th century: from Latin siphunculus ‘small tube’

definitions: (in shelled cephalopods such as nautiloids and ammonoids) a calcareous tube containing living tissue running through all the shell chambers, serving to pump fluid out of vacant chambers in order to adjust buoyancy.
shortDefinitions: (in shelled cephalopods such as nautiloids and ammonoids) calcareous tube containing living tissue running through all shell chambers
